 What is DECLARE?

👉 DECLARE is used to create a variable inside a function

DECLARE result INT;
  This means:

create a variable called result
its type is INT (it will store numbers)

Why do we use it?

👉 When you need to:

store a value temporarily
do calculations step by step
Example WITHOUT DECLARE  retune a+b;
Example WITH DECLARE
DECLARE result INT;
SET result = a + b;
RETURN result;
Easy Way to Remember
DECLARE → create variable
SET → give it value
RETURN → send result


Problem: Calculate discount

👉 If price > 100 → 20% discount
👉 else → 10%
DELIMITER //

CREATE FUNCTION finalPrice(p INT)
RETURNS INT
DETERMINISTIC
BEGIN
   IF p > 100 THEN
      RETURN p - (p * 0.2);
   ELSE
      RETURN p - (p * 0.1);
   END IF;
END //

DELIMITER ;

